subSubSection.paragraph:
Habitat.
Most records are from primary evergreen tropical rainforest habitat; T. Flannery reported one exception—a group “taken from a hole in a coconut palm in a plantation near disturbed forest.” On the Southeast Papuan Peninsula, Forbes’s Tree Mouse is restricted to hill forest mainly to ¢.700 m, and appears to be replaced above c.1000 m by its smaller congener, the Broad-headed Tree Mouse (
C. lamia
). On D’Entrecasteaux Islands, where it is the only recorded member of its genus, it extends to higher elevations, at least to 1300 m in lower montane rainforest on Goodenough Island (which peaks at 2531 m but remainsunsampled at high elevations). On Southeast Papuan Peninsula,it may be sympatric with the Lesser Tree Mouse (
C. vates
) in the Astrolabe Range.
